<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Exhaust System - Exhaust System - Removal and Installation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="17">
        <title>Removal and Installation</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Turbocharger Inlet Y-Pipe - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The names Turbocharger Inlet Y-Pipe and Turbocharger Adapter Pipe refer to the same
                        component.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0900002" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN00/N0028398.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger inlet gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger adapter pipe bolts (4 required)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger adapter pipe</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger adapter pipe nut (4 required)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger adapter pipe bolt (4 required)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust gas recirculation (EGR) cooler V-band clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler gas inlet gasket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise and support the vehicle with the transmission in NEUTRAL. For additional
                    information, refer to Jacking and Lifting in S10019.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the exhaust system. For additional information, refer to Exhaust System in this
                    section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger adapter pipe bolts.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Remove and discard the turbocharger inlet gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900020" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN00/N0019842.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the EGR cooler V-band clamp. Discard the gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0019845.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>LH shown, RH similar.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 4 turbocharger adapter pipe bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0018843.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger adapter pipe.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Turbocharger Inlet Y-Pipe - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the turbocharger adapter pipe.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Apply anti-seize lubricant to the bolt threads prior to installing.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>LH shown, RH similar.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the 4 turbocharger adapter pipe bolts, alternating between bolts, in 3 stages:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Stage 1: Tighten all bolts to 9 Nm (80 lb-in).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Stage 2: Tighten all bolts and additional 18 Nm (13 lb-ft)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Stage 3: Tighten all bolts a final 27 Nm (20 lb-ft)</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN00/N0018843.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Install a new turbocharger adapter pipe to EGR cooler gasket.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the EGR cooler gasket and install the EGR cooler V-band clamp.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten to 12 Nm (9 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900024" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0019845.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Apply anti-seize lubricant to the bolt threads prior to installing.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Install a new turbocharger inlet gasket.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the turbocharger inlet gasket and install the turbocharger adapter pipe
                    bolts.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten to 49 Nm (36 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900025" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0019842.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the exhaust system. For additional information, refer to Exhaust System in this
                    section.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Exhaust System - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>The normal operating temperature of the exhaust system is very high. Never attempt to service
                        any part of the system until it has cooled. Be especially careful when working around the
                        catalytic converter and muffler assembly. The temperature of the catalytic converter and muffler
                        assembly rises to a high level after only a few minutes of engine operation. Failure to follow
                        these instructions may result in personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not use oil or grease-based lubricants on the isolators. These lubricants may cause
                        deterioration of the rubber. This can lead to separation of the isolator from the exhaust hanger
                        bracket during vehicle operation.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise and support the vehicle with the transmission in NEUTRAL. For additional
                    information, refer to Jacking and Lifting in S10019.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transmission fluid indicator and bolt.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900026" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN00/N0023755.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the bolt and remove the transmission indicator tube.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Plug or cap the opening as needed.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900027" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023756.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the exhaust pipe at the exhaust pipe-to-catalytic converter and muffler assembly
                    joint.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the exhaust pipe-to-catalytic converter and muffler assembly coupling.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900028" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0028389.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the 2 catalytic converter and muffler assembly isolator hangers, and remove
                    the catalytic converter and muffler assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900029" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0017212.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the exhaust pipe retaining nuts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900030" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0017211.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the exhaust pipe and discard the turbocharger outlet gasket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Exhaust System - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the mating surface of the turbocharger-to-exhaust pipe.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Install a new turbocharger outlet gasket.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the new turbocharger outlet gasket and the exhaust pipe.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Apply anti-seize lubricant to the turbocharger-to-exhaust pipe stud threads prior to
                        installing the nuts.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the exhaust pipe retaining nuts.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten to 45 Nm (33 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900031" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN00/N0017211.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not tighten the coupling until all components are assembled.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Using an abrasive pad, clean the exhaust pipe-to-catalytic converter and muffler assembly
                        mating surfaces of any surface rust.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the catalytic converter and muffler assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900032" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0017212.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the exhaust system. For additional information, refer to Exhaust System Alignment
                    in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the exhaust pipe-to-catalytic converter and muffler assembly coupling.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten to 61 Nm (45 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900033" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0028389.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cap or plug. Install the transmission indicator tube and tighten the bolt.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten to 47 Nm (35 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900034" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023756.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the bolt and the transmission fluid indicator.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900035" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023755.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
